<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4610833>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 33. Holotype mandibles of Delotrochanter petersoni (CM 1603), with left canine, p1 and m1, and alveoli for p2–p4, from the Monroe Creek beds (fide Peterson, 1907), head of Warbonnet Creek, Sioux Co., Nebraska. A, labial view and B, high oblique lingual view of left mandible and the alveoli of right mandible. The m1 lacks a metaconid." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4610833/files/figure.png" .

